						               													<description>Green is the first game of the GreenGreenerGreenest set. Green, Greener and Greenest are three games that use the same set of components.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Green is a game for 3 players derived from The House of the Flying Blades and brother game of RED and BLUE, by the same designer, that uses a non-transitive capturing mechanism.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Depending on the set, you&amp;rsquo;d have:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Basic: a 6&amp;times;6 board, 15 black pyramids, 20 green pyramids, 15 white pyramids.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Advanced: a 6&amp;times;9 &amp;ndash; 9&amp;times;9 board (using one or both pads), 30 black pyramids, 45 green pyramids, 30 white pyramids.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay overview:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board starts full of pyramids. Players in turn capture (mandatory) other pyramids or stacks of pyramids orthogonally so that:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Black can only capture Green&amp;#10;- Green can only capture White&amp;#10;- White can only capture Black&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when all players pass in succession. The player with the highest combined height of controlled stacks wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Please refer to the rulebook for detailed rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
